ory>Algorithm</category> <category>Note</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Note: Grokking Algorithms&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is my note for the book grokking algorithms. It is really a nice book. It gives most of the fundamental concepts in simple terms. My number one recommendation for any one who is starting data stractures and algorithms.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://nabilseid.github.io/blog/2024/02/19/note-grokking-algorithms/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2024 16:42:20 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://nabilseid.github.io/feed_rss_updated.xml">African Sun</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://nabilseid.github.io/blog/2024/02/19/note-grokking-algorithms/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Notes: Zero-ETL</title> <author>almightyPush</author> <category>ETL</category> <category>Note</category> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Notes: Zero-ETL&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;At the time of writing Zero ETL is an integration tool that makes transactional data available in Redshift in near real time. This is useful if real time analytical data in Redshift is necessary. It support Aurora and RDS MySQL as data source.&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://nabilseid.github.io/blog/2024/02/06/notes-zero-etl/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 May 2024 16:42:20 +0000</pubDate><source url="https://nabilseid.github.io/feed_rss_updated.xml">African Sun</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://nabilseid.github.io/blog/2024/02/06/notes-zero-etl/</guid> </item> </channel></rss>